	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-07-13T06:58:20">Scapa Group plc is a United Kingdom-based holding company for a group of companies operating in the manufacture of bonding materials and solutions. The Company's products include bonding solutions used in wiring harness for electrical distribution, seat heating systems and assembly applications. Its segments include Healthcare, Industrial and Electronics. The Company's Healthcare segment develops and manufactures healthcare technologies for core markets, including advanced wound care, medical device, consumer wellness and drug delivery. Its Industrial segment focuses on the sectors, which include automotive, cable, construction and specialty products. The Company's Electronics segment engages with electronics manufacturers in the development stages of a product. The Company operates in Europe, North America and Asia. Its subsidiaries include Scapa Group Holdings GmbH, Scapa Holdings GmbH and Scapa North America Inc, among others.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-11-25T07:17:31">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 September 2015, Scapa Group plc revenues increased 4% to L119.3M. Net income decreased 48% to L2.1M. Revenues reflect Healthcare segment increase of 21% to L43.4M, Industrial segment increase of 5% to L75.9M, North America segment increase of 8% to L62M, Asia segment increase of 4% to L7.3M. Net income was offset by Industrial segment income decrease of 93% to L300K.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
